OL,3,CMeet the 85-year-old fighting lung
OL,4,Cdisease through dance
OL,6,FGlen attends classes designed to help
OL,7,Fimprove the breathing and mobility of
OL,8,Fpatients with COPD, or chronic
OL,9,Fobstructive pulmonary disease, which
OL,10,Fis the third leading cause of death
OL,11,Fworldwide.
OL,13,FThe disease cannot be cured, but if
OL,14,Fcaught early its effects can be
OL,15,Fmitigated.
OL,17,FThrough exercise, weight training and
OL,18,Fdance, Glen's stamina has improved and
OL,19,Fhe's left breathless less often.
