OL,3,CMeet the 85-year-old fighting lung
OL,4,Cdisease through dance
OL,6,FThe NHS urges anyone with persistent
OL,7,Fbreathlessness, a chronic cough, or
OL,8,Fongoing respiratory symptoms to speak
OL,9,Fto their GP, as early treatment can
OL,10,Fhelp deal with the effects of lung
OL,11,Fconditions.
OL,13,FIn his ninth decade and cutting a
OL,14,Fspritely figure, Glen is living proof
OL,15,Fthat with the right help, incurable
OL,16,Fdiseases need not stop someone living
OL,17,Fa normal life.
